<TITLE> Admn review panel wants over 100 restored </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)A high-level review committee has recommended putting over 100 senior civil servants, whop were retired by the BNP-led coalition government, back in the job. Dr Alauddin Ahmed, the adviser to the prime minister who chaired the review, said Monday the list included senior police officers. They will be in addition to those who have already been restored to their position as well as promoted with retrospective effect. The meeting made recommendations to resolve the issues of 41 admin cadre officers and 74 police cadre officers forced to retire in 2001-6, and also of 28 others who won court verdicts. It observed that scrutiny of the cases of nearly 6000 promotion-deprived officers was going on, said a press statement issued by the establishment ministry. bd
